# Repository Orchestration

## Required Orchestration
- Do not rely on automatic skill discovery for repository workflows.
- Choose an explicit project skill before making substantive changes.

## Use these project skills
- For new feature creation or multi-module feature scaffolding:
  - `.cursor/skills/feature-scaffolding-orchestrator/SKILL.md`
- For edits or review passes on an existing feature:
  - `.cursor/skills/feature-edit-review-orchestrator/SKILL.md`
- For changes under `common/**`:
  - `.cursor/skills/common-module-orchestrator/SKILL.md`
- For creating a non-feature shared module:
  - `.cursor/skills/module-scaffolding-orchestrator/SKILL.md`
- For changes under `server/`:
  - `.cursor/skills/server-ktor-orchestrator/SKILL.md`
- For final Gradle/KMP verification and structure checks:
  - `.cursor/skills/repo-verification-orchestrator/SKILL.md`

## Required subagent usage
- Do not run all reviewer/enforcer subagents by default.
- Use the selected project skill to choose the smallest valid set of subagents.
- Re-run the same subagents after fixes when the first pass reports concrete issues.

## Root integration policy
- When a task changes module structure or app integration, explicitly review:
  - `settings.gradle.kts`
  - `composeApp/build.gradle.kts`
  - `composeApp/.../di/AppModules.kt`
  - `common/core-navigation`
  - `composeApp/.../roating`

## Verification policy
- Before declaring work complete, invoke `.cursor/skills/repo-verification-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.
- Run targeted Gradle verification for touched modules.
- Run the structure check script when the change adds modules, renames modules, or modifies root integration.
